Fill a large #saucepan{} with water and bring to the boil with @salt{1/4%tsp} for the
pasta. Once boiling, add the @rigatoni pasta{200%g} to the pan and cook for
~{12%minutes}. Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and drizzle with a little @oil{}.

Meanwhile, drain and rinse the @sweetcorn{1%ear} in a #sieve{}. Halve, peel and
thinly slice the @onion{1}(halved and thinly sliced). Peel and grate the
@garlic clove{1}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Roughly chop the
@coriander{1%bunch}(roughly chopped) (stalks and all).

Put a large #frying pan{} on high heat (no oil). Once hot, add the
@diced chorizo{120%g} and sweetcorn to the pan. Fry until both the chorizo and
sweetcorn are starting to brown, ~{4-5%minutes}, stirring occasionally.

Once browned, lower the heat to medium. Add the onion to the pan. Cook until
softened, ~{3-4%minutes}, stirring occasionally. Mix in the garlic and a pinch
of @chilli flakes{pinch} (careful, they're hot!). Cook for ~{30%seconds}.
Stir in the @baby spinach{1%bunch}, 1 handful at a time, until wilted.

Once the spinach has wilted, add the @creme fraiche{150%g}, @water{50%ml} and the
@chicken stock powder{1/2%tsp} into the pan. Stir to dissolve the stock powder.
Bring to the boil then remove from the heat. Mix in half the coriander and half
the @hard Italian style cheese{1%50g}(grated). Season to taste with salt and
@pepper{}.

Add the drained pasta to the frying pan and gently mix until well coated in the
sauce. Reheat quickly if necessary. Serve in large #bowls{} with the remaining
coriander and hard Italian cheese sprinkled on top. Enjoy!

> The smooth, creamy taste of the pasta sauce made with creme fraiche compliments
> the stronger flavours of smoky chorizo, charred sweetcorn and garlic. Spinach
> adds a slight bitterness that works perfectly with the creaminess and an extra
> dose of veggies. With a total cooking time of 20 minutes, this dish is minimal
> effort and maximum flavour!